# Chinese Conditional Statements Compared to Polish

## Key Difference (Overview)

- **Chinese conditionals** are built with **particles and word order**, not verb tense changes.
  Common patterns: **如果 / 要是 / 假如 … (就 / 才 / 也 / 会 …)**.
- **Polish conditionals** rely on:
  - **Present/Future conditionals** with *jeśli / jeżeli*
  - **Hypothetical or unreal conditionals** with **gdyby + conditional mood (-by)**

---

## 1. Real / Possible Condition — 如果 … 就 …

### Chinese
如果下雨，我就不去。

### Polish
Jeśli będzie padać, nie pójdę.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 如果 (rúguǒ) — if  
- 下雨 (xià yǔ) — rain  
- 我 (wǒ) — I  
- 就 (jiù) — then  
- 不 (bù) — not  
- 去 (qù) — go  

### English
If it rains, I won’t go.

### Grammar Note
- **如果 … 就 …** is the most neutral real condition.
- Polish uses **jeśli** + future tense verb.

---

## 2. Real Condition with Habitual Result — 要是 … 就 …

### Chinese
要是你努力学习，就会成功。

### Polish
Jeśli będziesz pilnie się uczyć, odniesiesz sukces.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 要是 (yàoshi) — if  
- 你 (nǐ) — you  
- 努力 (nǔlì) — diligently  
- 学习 (xuéxí) — study  
- 就会 (jiù huì) — then will  
- 成功 (chénggōng) — succeed  

### English
If you study hard, you will succeed.

### Grammar Note
- **会** often appears in results that are **predictive or general**.
- Polish expresses this with future tense in both clauses.

---

## 3. Necessary Condition — 只有 … 才 …

### Chinese
只有努力，才能成功。

### Polish
Tylko jeśli będziesz się starać, osiągniesz sukces.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 只有 (zhǐyǒu) — only if  
- 努力 (nǔlì) — make effort  
- 才 (cái) — only then  
- 能 (néng) — can  
- 成功 (chénggōng) — succeed  

### English
Only if you make an effort can you succeed.

### Grammar Note
- **才** emphasizes that the result happens **only under this condition**.
- Polish uses *tylko jeśli* + future tense.

---

## 4. Negative Result — 如果不 … 就不 …

### Chinese
如果你不来，我就不走。

### Polish
Jeśli nie przyjdziesz, nie wyjdę.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 如果 (rúguǒ) — if  
- 你 (nǐ) — you  
- 不来 (bù lái) — don’t come  
- 我 (wǒ) — I  
- 就 (jiù) — then  
- 不走 (bù zǒu) — won’t leave  

### English
If you don’t come, I won’t leave.

### Grammar Note
- Chinese uses **不** consistently; no tense shift.
- Polish future tense is conjugated in both verbs.

---

## 5. Alternative Outcome — 否则 (Otherwise)

### Chinese
快点走，否则会迟到。

### Polish
Idź szybciej, inaczej spóźnimy się.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 快点 (kuài diǎn) — hurry up  
- 走 (zǒu) — go  
- 否则 (fǒuzé) — otherwise  
- 会 (huì) — will  
- 迟到 (chídào) — be late  

### English
Hurry up, otherwise we’ll be late.

### Grammar Note
- **否则** introduces a **negative conditional result**.
- Polish uses *inaczej* or *w przeciwnym razie*.

---

## 6. Hypothetical / Unreal Condition — 要是 … 就 …

### Chinese
要是我有时间，就帮你了。

### Polish
Gdybym miał czas, pomógłbym ci.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 要是 (yàoshi) — if  
- 我 (wǒ) — I  
- 有 (yǒu) — have  
- 时间 (shíjiān) — time  
- 就 (jiù) — then  
- 帮 (bāng) — help  
- 你 (nǐ) — you  
- 了 (le) — unrealized outcome marker  

### English
If I had time, I would help you.

### Grammar Note
- Chinese signals unreality through **context + 了**.
- Polish **requires conditional mood** (*-bym, -byś*).

---

## 7. Past Unreal Condition — 如果当时 … 就 …

### Chinese
如果当时告诉我，我就不会犯错了。

### Polish
Gdybyś mi wtedy powiedział, nie popełniłbym błędu.

### Word-by-word (Gloss)
- 如果 (rúguǒ) — if  
- 当时 (dāngshí) — at that time  
- 告诉 (gàosu) — tell  
- 我 (wǒ) — me  
- 就 (jiù) — then  
- 不会 (bú huì) — would not  
- 犯错 (fàn cuò) — make a mistake  
- 了 (le) — counterfactual marker  

### English
If you had told me then, I wouldn’t have made a mistake.

### Grammar Note
- Chinese relies on **time words + 不会 + 了**.
- Polish uses **double conditional + past reference**.

---

## Summary Table (Conceptual)

- Chinese conditionals = **particles + structure**
- Polish conditionals = **verb mood and tense**
- Chinese verbs **never change**
- Polish verbs **must change form**

